.SH NAME
todo \- a simple command\-line todo list manager
.SH SYNOPSIS
\f[B]todo\f[R] [\f[B]\-v\f[R] | \f[B]\(enversion\f[R]] [\f[B]\-h\f[R] |
\f[B]\(enhelp\f[R]] \f[I]command\f[R] [\f[I]args\f[R]]
.SH DESCRIPTION
\f[B]todo\f[R] is a command\-line todo list manager written in Zig.
It provides a simple yet powerful interface for managing tasks with
support for tags, deadlines, and Human\-Readable Unique Identifiers
(HUIDs).
Todo lists are stored locally in a \f[B].todo\f[R] directory in the
current working directory.
.SH OPTIONS
\f[B]\-h\f[R], \f[B]\(enhelp\f[R]
.PD 0
.P
.PD
Display help information and exit.
.PP
\f[B]\-v\f[R], \f[B]\(enversion\f[R]
.PD 0
.P
.PD
Display version information and exit.
.PP
\f[B]\-vh\f[R]
.PD 0
.P
.PD
Display both version and extended help information (options can be
grouped).
.SH COMMANDS
.SS init
\f[B]todo init\f[R]
.PP
Initialize a new todo list in the current directory by creating a
\f[B].todo\f[R] directory with necessary files.
If the directory already exists, existing files will not be overwritten.
.SS add
\f[B]todo add \-m\f[R] \f[I]message\f[R] [\f[B]\-t\f[R] \f[I]tags\f[R]]
[\f[B]\-d\f[R] \f[I]deadline\f[R]]
.PP
Add a new todo item with the specified description, optional tags, and
optional deadline.
Returns the generated HUID for the new item.
.PP
\f[B]Options:\f[R] \- \f[B]\-m\f[R], \f[B]\(enmessage\f[R]
\f[I]message\f[R] \- Description of the todo item (required) \-
\f[B]\-t\f[R], \f[B]\(entags\f[R] \f[I]tag1,tag2,\&...\f[R] \-
Comma\-separated list of tags (optional) \- \f[B]\-d\f[R],
\f[B]\(endeadline\f[R] \f[I]HUID\f[R] \- Deadline in HUID format
(optional) \- \f[B]\-h\f[R], \f[B]\(enhelp\f[R] \- Display help for this
command
.PP
\f[B]Example:\f[R]
.IP
.EX
$ todo add \-m \(dqFinish the report\(dq \-t work,urgent \-d 20210701\-120000
Todo item added with HUID: 20210630\-170000
.EE
.SS list
\f[B]todo list\f[R] [\f[B]\-l\f[R]] [\f[B]\-a\f[R]] [\f[B]\-d\f[R]]
[\f[B]\-s\f[R]] [\f[B]\-t\f[R]] [\f[B]\-u\f[R]]
.PP
List all todo items with optional filters and display options.
By default, only shows open (not completed or canceled) items.
.PP
\f[B]Options:\f[R] \- \f[B]\-a\f[R], \f[B]\(enall\f[R] \- Show all items
including completed and canceled ones \- \f[B]\-d\f[R],
\f[B]\(endeadline\f[R] \- Show the deadline of each item \-
\f[B]\-h\f[R], \f[B]\(enhelp\f[R] \- Display help for this command \-
\f[B]\-l\f[R], \f[B]\(enlong\f[R] \- Show detailed information
(equivalent to \-dstu) \- \f[B]\-s\f[R], \f[B]\(enstatus\f[R] \- Show
the completion status of each item \- \f[B]\-t\f[R], \f[B]\(entags\f[R]
\- Show the tags associated with each item \- \f[B]\-u\f[R],
\f[B]\(enhuid\f[R] \- Show the HUID of each item
.PP
\f[B]Note:\f[R] The \f[B]\-l\f[R] option can only be combined with
\f[B]\-a\f[R]; it implies all other display options.
.PP
\f[B]Status Indicators:\f[R] \- \f[B][ ]\f[R] \- Open item \-
\f[B][x]\f[R] \- Completed item \- \f[B][\-]\f[R] \- Canceled item
.PP
\f[B]Example:\f[R]
.IP
.EX
$ todo list \-a \-s \-u
.EE
.SS finish
\f[B]todo finish\f[R] [\f[B]\-u\f[R]] \f[I]huid\f[R]
.PP
Mark a todo item as completed.
.PP
\f[B]Options:\f[R] \- \f[B]\-u\f[R], \f[B]\(enhuid\f[R] \f[I]HUID\f[R]
\- HUID of the item to complete (flag is optional) \- \f[B]\-h\f[R],
\f[B]\(enhelp\f[R] \- Display help for this command
.PP
\f[B]Example:\f[R]
.IP
.EX
$ todo finish 20210630\-170000
Todo item with HUID 20210630\-170000 has been marked as completed.
.EE
.SS cancel
\f[B]todo cancel\f[R] [\f[B]\-u\f[R]] \f[I]huid\f[R]
.PP
Cancel a todo item.
Unlike completion, cancellation indicates the task was abandoned rather
than finished.
.PP
\f[B]Options:\f[R] \- \f[B]\-u\f[R], \f[B]\(enhuid\f[R] \f[I]HUID\f[R]
\- HUID of the item to cancel (flag is optional) \- \f[B]\-h\f[R],
\f[B]\(enhelp\f[R] \- Display help for this command
.PP
\f[B]Example:\f[R]
.IP
.EX
$ todo cancel 20210630\-170000
Todo item with HUID 20210630\-170000 has been canceled.
.EE
.SS edit
\f[B]todo edit \-u\f[R] \f[I]huid\f[R] [\f[B]\-m\f[R] \f[I]message\f[R]]
[\f[B]\-t\f[R] \f[I]tags\f[R]] [\f[B]\-d\f[R] \f[I]deadline\f[R]]
[\f[B]\-n\f[R]] [\f[B]\-c\f[R]] [\f[B]\-x\f[R]] [\f[B]\-o\f[R]]
.PP
Edit an existing todo item.
You can update the description, tags, deadline, or change its status.
.PP
\f[B]Options:\f[R] \- \f[B]\-u\f[R], \f[B]\(enhuid\f[R] \f[I]HUID\f[R]
\- HUID of the item to edit (required) \- \f[B]\-m\f[R],
\f[B]\(enmessage\f[R] \f[I]message\f[R] \- New description (optional) \-
\f[B]\-t\f[R], \f[B]\(entags\f[R] \f[I]tag1,tag2,\&...\f[R] \- New
comma\-separated list of tags (optional) \- \f[B]\-d\f[R],
\f[B]\(endeadline\f[R] \f[I]HUID\f[R] | \f[B]x\f[R] \- New deadline in
HUID format, or `x' to remove (optional) \- \f[B]\-n\f[R],
\f[B]\(enappend\f[R] \- Append to existing tags instead of replacing
them \- \f[B]\-c\f[R], \f[B]\(encomplete\f[R] \- Mark the item as
completed \- \f[B]\-x\f[R], \f[B]\(encancel\f[R] \- Mark the item as
canceled \- \f[B]\-o\f[R], \f[B]\(enopen\f[R] \- Mark the item as open
(overrides \-c and \-x) \- \f[B]\-h\f[R], \f[B]\(enhelp\f[R] \- Display
help for this command
.PP
\f[B]Note:\f[R] Options \f[B]\-c\f[R], \f[B]\-x\f[R], \f[B]\-o\f[R], and
\f[B]\-n\f[R] can be combined.
When \f[B]\-o\f[R] is used, \f[B]\-c\f[R] and \f[B]\-x\f[R] cannot be in
the same option group.
.PP
\f[B]Example:\f[R]
.IP
.EX
$ todo edit \-u 20210630\-170000 \-m \(dqFinish the updated report\(dq \-c
.EE
.SS remove
\f[B]todo remove\f[R] [\f[B]\-u\f[R]] \f[I]huid\f[R]
.PP
Permanently remove a todo item from the list.
This operation cannot be undone.
.PP
\f[B]Options:\f[R] \- \f[B]\-u\f[R], \f[B]\(enhuid\f[R] \f[I]HUID\f[R]
\- HUID of the item to remove (flag is optional) \- \f[B]\-h\f[R],
\f[B]\(enhelp\f[R] \- Display help for this command
.PP
\f[B]Example:\f[R]
.IP
.EX
$ todo remove 20210630\-170000
Todo item with HUID 20210630\-170000 has been removed.
.EE
.SS defer
\f[B]todo defer\f[R] [\f[B]\-u\f[R]] \f[I]huid\f[R] [\f[B]\-w\f[R]
\f[I]weeks\f[R]] [\f[B]\-D\f[R] \f[I]days\f[R]] [\f[B]\-H\f[R]
\f[I]hours\f[R]] [\f[B]\-m\f[R] \f[I]minutes\f[R]] [\f[B]\-S\f[R]
\f[I]seconds\f[R]]
.PP
Defer the deadline of a todo item by a specified duration.
The item must have an existing deadline.
.PP
\f[B]Options:\f[R] \- \f[B]\-u\f[R], \f[B]\(enhuid\f[R] \f[I]HUID\f[R]
\- HUID of the item to defer (flag is optional) \- \f[B]\-w\f[R],
\f[B]\(enweeks\f[R] \f[I]N\f[R] \- Number of weeks to extend \-
\f[B]\-D\f[R], \f[B]\(endays\f[R] \f[I]N\f[R] \- Number of days to
extend \- \f[B]\-H\f[R], \f[B]\(enhours\f[R] \f[I]N\f[R] \- Number of
hours to extend \- \f[B]\-m\f[R], \f[B]\(enminutes\f[R] \f[I]N\f[R] \-
Number of minutes to extend \- \f[B]\-S\f[R], \f[B]\(enseconds\f[R]
\f[I]N\f[R] \- Number of seconds to extend \- \f[B]\-h\f[R],
\f[B]\(enhelp\f[R] \- Display help for this command
.PP
\f[B]Example:\f[R]
.IP
.EX
$ todo defer 20210630\-170000 \-D 3 \-H 5
Todo item with HUID 20210630\-170000 has been deferred to new deadline 20210703\-220000.
.EE
.SS grep
\f[B]todo grep\f[R] [\f[B]\-a\f[R]] [\f[B]\-b\f[R]] [\f[B]\-i\f[R]]
[\f[B]\-m\f[R]] [\f[B]\-t\f[R]] [\f[B]\-s\f[R] \f[I]status\f[R]]
[\f[B]\-d\f[R] \f[I]deadline\f[R]] [\f[B]\-u\f[R] \f[I]huid\f[R]]
[\f[I]keyword\f[R]]
.PP
Search todo items by keyword in description or tags with optional
filters.
.PP
\f[B]Options:\f[R] \- \f[B]\-a\f[R], \f[B]\(enall\f[R] \- Include
inactive items (completed or canceled) \- \f[B]\-b\f[R],
\f[B]\(enboth\f[R] \- Search keyword in both description and tags \-
\f[B]\-i\f[R], \f[B]\(enignore\-case\f[R] \- Perform case\-insensitive
search \- \f[B]\-m\f[R], \f[B]\(enmessage\f[R] \- Search keyword in
description only \- \f[B]\-t\f[R], \f[B]\(entags\f[R] \- Search keyword
in tags only \- \f[B]\-s\f[R], \f[B]\(enstatus\f[R] \f[I]status\f[R] \-
Filter by status: `o' (open), `c' (completed), `x' (canceled) \-
\f[B]\-d\f[R], \f[B]\(endeadline\f[R] \f[I]HUID\f[R] \- Filter by
deadline \- \f[B]\-u\f[R], \f[B]\(enhuid\f[R] \f[I]HUID\f[R] \- Filter
by specific HUID \- \f[B]\-h\f[R], \f[B]\(enhelp\f[R] \- Display help
for this command
.PP
\f[B]Note:\f[R] Options \f[B]\-a\f[R], \f[B]\-b\f[R], \f[B]\-i\f[R],
\f[B]\-m\f[R], and \f[B]\-t\f[R] can be combined.
When \f[B]\-b\f[R] is used, \f[B]\-m\f[R] and \f[B]\-t\f[R] cannot be in
the same option group.
.PP
\f[B]Example:\f[R]
.IP
.EX
$ todo grep \-ti report
.EE
.SS remind
\f[B]todo remind\f[R] [\f[B]\-s\f[R] \f[I]start\f[R]] [\f[B]\-e\f[R]
\f[I]end\f[R]] [\f[B]\-u\f[R]] [\f[B]\-t\f[R]] [\f[B]\-d\f[R]]
.PP
Show todo items that are due within a specified time range.
Useful for checking upcoming deadlines.
.PP
\f[B]Options:\f[R] \- \f[B]\-s\f[R], \f[B]\(enstart\f[R] \f[I]HUID\f[R]
\- Start of time range in HUID format (inclusive) \- \f[B]\-e\f[R],
\f[B]\(enend\f[R] \f[I]HUID\f[R] \- End of time range in HUID format
(inclusive) \- \f[B]\-u\f[R], \f[B]\(enhuid\f[R] \- Show the HUID of
each item \- \f[B]\-t\f[R], \f[B]\(entags\f[R] \- Show the tags of each
item \- \f[B]\-d\f[R], \f[B]\(endeadline\f[R] \- Show the deadline of
each item \- \f[B]\-h\f[R], \f[B]\(enhelp\f[R] \- Display help for this
command
.PP
\f[B]Note:\f[R] Options \f[B]\-u\f[R], \f[B]\-t\f[R], and \f[B]\-d\f[R]
can be combined.
.PP
\f[B]Example:\f[R]
.IP
.EX
$ todo remind \-s 20210701\-000000 \-e 20210707\-235959
.EE
.SS huid
\f[B]todo huid\f[R]
.PP
Generate a new Human\-Readable Unique Identifier (HUID) based on the
current time.
HUIDs use the format YYYYMMDD\-HHMMSS.
.PP
\f[B]Note:\f[R] To avoid conflicts, HUIDs should not be generated in
rapid succession.
.PP
\f[B]Example:\f[R]
.IP
.EX
$ todo huid
20231220\-153045
.EE
.SS author
\f[B]todo author\f[R]
.PP
Display author information.
.SS version
\f[B]todo version\f[R]
.PP
Display version information including the build version and Zig compiler
version.
.SS help
\f[B]todo help\f[R]
.PP
Display the main help message.
.SH HUID FORMAT
Human\-Readable Unique Identifiers (HUIDs) use the format
\f[B]YYYYMMDD\-HHMMSS\f[R], where: \- \f[B]YYYY\f[R] \- Four\-digit year
\- \f[B]MM\f[R] \- Two\-digit month (01\-12) \- \f[B]DD\f[R] \-
Two\-digit day (01\-31) \- \f[B]HH\f[R] \- Two\-digit hour in 24\-hour
format (00\-23) \- \f[B]MM\f[R] \- Two\-digit minute (00\-59) \-
\f[B]SS\f[R] \- Two\-digit second (00\-59)
.PP
\f[B]Example:\f[R] 20210630\-170000 represents June 30, 2021 at 5:00:00
PM.
.SH SHORT OPTION GROUPING
Most single\-letter options can be grouped together for convenience: \-
\f[B]\-asu\f[R] is equivalent to \f[B]\-a \-s \-u\f[R] \- \f[B]\-vh\f[R]
is equivalent to \f[B]\-v \-h\f[R] \- \f[B]\-abim\f[R] is equivalent to
\f[B]\-a \-b \-i \-m\f[R]
.PP
Some commands have restrictions on which options can be grouped
together.
Refer to individual command help for details.
.SH FILES
\f[B].todo/\f[R]
.PD 0
.P
.PD
Directory created by \f[B]todo init\f[R] that stores all todo list data.
This directory should not be manually modified.
.SH EXIT STATUS
\f[B]0\f[R]
.PD 0
.P
.PD
Success
.PP
\f[B]1\f[R]
.PD 0
.P
.PD
General error (invalid arguments, item not found, etc.)
.SH EXAMPLES
Initialize a new todo list:
.IP
.EX
$ todo init
.EE
.PP
Add a todo item with tags and deadline:
.IP
.EX
$ todo add \-m \(dqSubmit quarterly report\(dq \-t work,urgent \-d 20240115\-170000
.EE
.PP
List all open items with full details:
.IP
.EX
$ todo list \-l
.EE
.PP
Search for items tagged with \(lqwork\(rq:
.IP
.EX
$ todo grep \-t work
.EE
.PP
Mark an item as completed:
.IP
.EX
$ todo finish 20240115\-170000
.EE
.PP
Defer a deadline by 2 days:
.IP
.EX
$ todo defer 20240115\-170000 \-D 2
.EE
.PP
Edit an item\(cqs description and add tags:
.IP
.EX
$ todo edit \-u 20240115\-170000 \-m \(dqSubmit updated report\(dq \-t work,urgent,reviewed \-n
.EE
.PP
Show items due this week:
.IP
.EX
$ todo remind \-s 20240108\-000000 \-e 20240114\-235959 \-utd
.EE
